##New Crown Epidemic Prevention to the countryside: Wuhan hundreds of kilometers away, a county prevention and control logs

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* One County with a million people has the highest number of confirmed cases in the city. In Wuhan, there was a shortage of beds, supplies were in short supply, and virus detection was difficult. In this county, it all happened again.

* Village Road Closure, publicity epidemic, organizational isolation, sterilization, household investigation... a resident village cadres feel: All aspects have reached the limit.

Nearly 700,000 Huanggang residents returned home from Wuhan on January 23, before the city was shut down, bringing back the new crown disease. The returnees are spread across 10 counties and cities in Huanggang.

One County with a million people has the highest number of confirmed cases in the city. In Wuhan, there was a shortage of beds, supplies were in short supply, and virus detection was difficult. In this county, it all happened again.

The majority of the population in the county is distributed in towns and rural areas, a wide space, the grass-roots prevention and control forces are relatively weak. The county sent cadres to more than 600 villages to assist in the supervision of the epidemic prevention work.

Closure of the village road, publicity, quarantine, sterilization, household investigation... a resident village cadres feel: All aspects have reached the limit.

On January 21,2020, the 27th day of the 12th Lunar Month, a county under the jurisdiction of Huanggang City in Hubei Province began to make a scene. People who work abroad returned home one after another. They must catch the 28th day of the 12th Lunar Month and return home to "return the blessings" .

"return blessings" is the most solemn day during the local Spring Festival, on which people eat "fat rice" . Early in the morning, every family will close the door, put on the chicken, duck, fish sacrifice ancestors, its happy to eat a meal, after eating can open the door, set off firecrackers, blessing the new year.

They had no idea that a huge epidemic was looming.

Li Cheng (not his real name) , who lives and works in the county town, went to the railway station on the night of the 28th of the 12th month and picked up the children working in Jiangsu Province. He said later that he would not have allowed his son to return to Hubei if he had known the situation was so serious.

Because of the outbreak, his son was unable to return to work in Jiangsu after the Lunar New Year holiday, but the family still spent only a handful of time together. Ten days later, Li Cheng will go to the countryside from the county seat, to carry out the mission of epidemic prevention in the village.

On January 30(the same day, Tang Zhihong, former director of Huanggang's Health Commission, was removed from his post) , the county issued an emergency notice requiring village-based cadres from all units to go to the village to assist in supervising the prevention and control of the epidemic in the town and village.

As of 2400 hours on January 30, a total of 573 new cases of pneumonia and 12 deaths had been reported in Huanggang, making it the worst case in the province except Wuhan. Li Cheng's county has reported 58 cases, ranking in the top five in Huanggang.

It is understood that nearly 700,000 Huanggang residents returned from Wuhan before the city was closed on January 23. They are scattered across the vast countryside of the 10 counties and urban areas under Huanggang's control. To the local rural grass-roots epidemic prevention work brought no small pressure.

Since the beginning of February, Li has been living in the village, helping to implement the control of traffic, publicity and epidemic prevention, House investigation and other work, but also to help the isolated villagers to buy living materials, medicine. Cadres like him who have been stationed in the village, as well as villagers who are about to return to work and plough in spring, are waiting for the end of the epidemic to be lifted as soon as possible.

The outbreak came from Wuhan

The first highly suspected new coronary case in the county occurred before January 16. Ding Qing, a doctor at the county people's Hospital, remembers clearly that the first patient was screened through a CT scan. "The hospital was already alert and immediately vacated the infection ward, set up 10 intensive care units, deployed 20 sets of medical facilities such as suction machines and monitors, started issuing medical masks and protective caps every day, and had a special person supervise doctors to wear them. "

There was nothing unusual in the town at this time, and there were very few people wearing masks on the streets. On January 17, Li also attended an event in Wuhan. A few days later, a few friends in Wuhan wanted to come over and play, specifically asked Li Cheng: Can Come? Li Cheng said without thinking: "You are not a virus, just come. "

However, in those days, the number of fever and cough patients in the county people's hospital suddenly increased, and Ding Qing's daily outpatient service increased from a few to twenty, mostly migrant workers returning from Wuhan.

On 19 January, all medical staff of the People's Hospital of the county took part in the study and training on coronaviruses as a matter of urgency, in accordance with a notification from their superiors. Also from that day on, the hospital's CT equipment began high-load operation. "Like this fever, cough patients, all the rules to do CT, the testing staff busy, every day light line for CT, there are more than 100... " Ding Qing said, the hospital soon filled with fever patients. "there were so many patients in the Department of Suction medicine that the doctors couldn't handle it. So they shut down the clinics of endocrinology, oncology and so on, and the doctors in these departments helped with triage. "

According to the County Epidemic Prevention Headquarters Arrangement, the county people's Hospital and the County Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine as the admission of new crown patients designated hospitals. The former is for severe cases and the latter for mild and suspected cases. Ding recalled that the infection department of the county people's Hospital had four floors and was soon filled with critically ill patients. In order to share the pressure, the county maternal and child health care hospital has also set up a pre-check-up triage and fever clinic. The township hospitals and community health service centers have set up pre-examination and triage clinics and fever clinics.

Once appeared in Wuhan bed shortage, material shortage, detection difficulties, with Wuhan a straight line distance of 100 kilometers away from this county, also all repeat.

Virus detection is a key indicator for the diagnosis of a patient. But around January 25, the county people's Hospital ran out of kits. "If we receive treatment, we can only do a test for H1N1 and H1N2, and nucleic acid reagents to detect the new coronavirus are scarce, " Ding said, adding that during this period, the criteria for admission to hospitals in the county were positive for nucleic acid tests. This, she believes, has allowed some of the invisible patients to roam about and spread the virus.

In early February, the kits were fully supplied, but the county people's Hospital was overwhelmed with just three inspectors. It is understood that COVID-19 nucleic acid testing laboratories must achieve at least Level 2 biosafety laboratory level, while using a third level of personal protection, in order to carry out testing. "The neighboring counties couldn't do the tests, so they had to send the samples to us for sampling during the day and testing at night, " Ding said.

Until mid-february, Shandong Medical Support Team (Shandong, Hunan counterpart aid Huanggang) came with supplies and sent three inspectors, virus detection pressure was released.

Bed space resources are also constantly shifting within the limited space. As of February 10, the county people's Hospital has vacated a total of three buildings, namely the infection department, the Oncology Department and the complex building, as a new coronary pneumonia ward (Shandong medical team later took over one of them) , each ward can accommodate 60 patients. A township health center more than 10 kilometers from the county seat was also rapidly requisitioned as a fixed-point institutions, as the fourth ward. As of 2400 hours on February 10,277 confirmed cases have been reported in the whole county.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Letter of appreciation from the patients in the isolation ward (provided by the interviewees)

Compared to the number of patients, beds are still tight. Based on the principle of "better prepared than used" , the county decided to urgently requisition the new hospital district under construction in the county maternal and Child Health Hospital and transform it into an emergency standby fixed-point hospital, which is expected to provide 200 beds.

The controls are escalating

The hospital is just the last line of defense against the epidemic. If we do not cut off the route of transmission of the virus, control the potential source of infection, no matter how much medical resources are invested, we will cut off the water supply.

On January 23, the county's COVID-19 issued notice No. 1, announcing a traffic control: From 0 a.m. the next day, county-wide bus, county and township passenger transport, long-distance passenger transport, taxi and ferry terminal suspended operations, the railway station from the county channel temporarily closed.

As in other areas, all entry and exit points within the county have also started to conduct vehicle and personnel checks, and take body temperature measurements of those entering and leaving. Those with fever symptoms are immediately arranged to designated medical sites for further diagnosis and treatment.

On January 31, traffic control was upgraded. According to the order of the Huanggang Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters, from 00:00 on that day, all the vehicles in the county town except those involved in epidemic prevention and control, medical treatment, life and production support, and emergency rescue, all other vehicles are prohibited. Each village group, Natural Bay, communities, residential areas in and out of the motor vehicle lane reserved only one emergency road, the rest of the road all closed.

County Epidemic Prevention Headquarters further requirements: The village groups, Natural Bay, communities, residential areas to implement closed management, road control, no special reason, people and vehicles are not allowed to enter.

The population of the county is one million, but the urban area is not large, the resident population is more than 200,000, the rest of the population is distributed in more than a dozen towns (districts,) , there are more than 600 administrative villages below. In other words, the focus and difficulty of prevention and control at the grass-roots level is in fact in the vast countryside.

Delta survey respondents

At the end of January, the county Epidemic Prevention Headquarters issued a circular to arrange for cadres to sink into the villages, each village to ensure that at least one state cadre enters the villages into the bay, and to urge the villagers (residents) committees and villagers'groups to make up for the deficiencies in the epidemic prevention and control work, "strengthen measures to strictly guard against the spread of the epidemic situation. ".

That's what Rhee went to the countryside to do.

A VILLAGE EPIDEMIC: 5 people, 1,738

Li Chengyao village, more than 20 kilometers away from the county seat, is also the village where he participated in poverty alleviation work last year. Every village in the county has been posted before the staff of poverty alleviation. "The headquarters ordered that the work of poverty alleviation be transferred to epidemic prevention, so we came down. "

As soon as he entered the village, Rhee met a villager who was not wearing a mask. County requirements of the "Ten all" , one of which is "all people out to wear a mask.

"I rolled down the window and asked him, he said smoking, and I said 'mask if you smoke! ' And he put it on, " Li wrote in his diary that day.

That morning, Li Cheng, the doctor of the town health center, and the village Party secretary, went to each group to stick up signs to promote "ten all the same. ". There are 10 teams in the village, all of them going at least 10 kilometers at a time. "As soon as the Gong went off, we had a lot of people looking at us, people looking at us from a distance, people opening half a door, looking out through the crack, people coming up and asking if it was a hair mask... "

The local "ten-all" Bulletin Board (provided by interviewees)

Li's work unit and the town government did issue masks one after another, more than enough for him and four village officials, but too little for the entire village. "There are 1,738 people in the village. How do you divide them? Masks are consumables. We can only give them to people on duty and hauling garbage. "

It is understood that 389 people in the village are returning from other places. In addition to screening these returnees, Li's main job was to go door to door, issuing thermometers to discourage Mah jongg players, fishermen, and people leaving the house without masks.

During the epidemic, coupled with the Spring Festival, the countryside gathered to play cards in many cases. According to the order of the superior, Li Chengde to collect Mahjong machine. But the automatic Mahjong machine is too bulky to handle. Li Cheng thought of a way: From a Mahjong collection up 10 cards, for custody, after the epidemic returned. "there was a little girl who was reading, and she said, 'do you have any legal basis for this? What am I supposed to say to her? I know what she meant, but there's no way around it at this point. ' "

To dissuade villagers from going out, Li Cheng said, at first simply can not persuade, 10 people can persuade half of the good, only later a little better.

There are special circumstances. Last week, on the second day of snow in Hubei Province, a villager in another village fell ill. Because of the isolation of the traffic and the lack of a car, his son and daughter-in-law wheeled him to the town health center. It takes the village more than an hour to walk to town with a cart.

Delta survey respondents

Starting at noon on February 14, epidemic prevention measures in the county were again upgraded and wartime control was implemented throughout the territory. As of 2400 hours on February 13, the county has reported a total of 308 confirmed cases (including 20 clinically confirmed cases) , a fourfold increase over two weeks ago.

Under wartime control, residents were confined to their homes and were forbidden to go out. If they violate the regulations, they will be sent to the county sports center for intensive education after being inspected by the patrol police. The list of those who violate the ban, as well as the names of their units and communities, are posted online daily. At present, more than 70 people in the county have accepted compulsory study.

Li Cheng added another piece of work  --. He and five village cadres are responsible for feeding 1,738 people in the village. The villagers one day in advance to the name of the necessary supplies, the number of the village committee, the village sent to the town to purchase.

Purchase list of villagers (provided by interviewees)

Some villagers are patients with chronic diseases, such as high blood pressure, heart disease, gout and so on, year-round to take medicine, need to buy medicine. Rhee will also help to buy for you. There's a health center in town, plus two local pharmacies. But there are new problems: for example, toothache is so common that the causes of toothache vary greatly. The town health center doesn't have a special dental department, and Li Cheng often doesn't know which medicine to buy, for example, gout patients need Colchicine, allopurinol and so on, "If you can't buy it, then gather the information into town, and then figure out how to do it. "

Buy On behalf of the villagers, but also caused a lot of ironic things. Either there is a demand for something so bizarre that some people buy strong birth control pills, or it is too expensive to buy something like pork, or they forget to pay and take it away.

"The village piled up a pile of Sanitary Napkins bought on behalf of a few days ago, and the person who went shopping was a man. He didn't understand what was particular about this thing. The person who wanted to use these things didn't say clearly about the size of sanitary Napkins. As a result, he bought a bunch of Sanitary Napkins. Only then did the fairies shyly say that the models didn't match, refused to accept the goods, didn't pay for them, and couldn't return them... "

It's like having an invisible enemy

For All the difficulties of working in the village, Li admits it was necessary for wartime control. "The virus, no one can see. "

Fortunately, so far, no new cases have been reported in the village where he was stationed. The village is located in the township, a total of 41 villages, of which 10 villages found a total of more than 10 cases. Li Cheng felt that the village where the case was found had a better job because everyone was afraid. Of course, it is also easy to go to the other extreme, such as the village between the road all sealed, or even block the door to return to the villagers.

The village where Sun Yi (not his real name) is based is not so lucky. "Also Fu" that afternoon, from Wuhan to work a couple back home, suddenly feel not very comfortable, sent to the hospital, the next day was diagnosed.

The village exploded. The villagers, who had close contact with the couple, volunteered to report it. That wouldn't have happened a few days ago. Because of the experience of being stationed in the village, Sun Yi is quite aware of the situation in the village, "There are people who are stubborn and can't stay at home, who like to go around and go fishing and can't be dissuaded. But once they have a confirmed patient, they are very active, shut down, self-isolation. The temperature is also quite cooperative, if there is an abnormal situation, report it in a timely manner."

According to the work flow, if the villagers'body temperature is abnormal, Sun Yi should report to the town government. After the town health center sends a unified team of special personnel to take body temperature measurements, they are then sent to the town health center for further examination. If the symptoms match, it goes straight to the county.

Sun Yi, who entered the village on Feb. 1, lives in the office of the village committee. Now I wake up at 8:30 a.m. Sharp, and the first thing I do is turn on the radio.

The Stereo Speaker, like a handle case, is on the third floor balcony of the village committee office building. "If you put the speakers on it, most of the village can hear it, " Sun said. In addition to the speaker from the village committee, there are seven speakers in the whole village, which are placed in various open spaces, the popular science propaganda contents such as "ten laws" and management of fever patients were broadcast in a circle for about 8 hours every day.

At first, the villagers are not used to, feel that every day put a little noisy. Sun Yi also felt noisy. Later, the content was updated, such as how to buy supplies, how to measure body temperature, and so on.

Li Chengzhu village, is in the road at the point of recording, "now no one is listening to, just to create momentum. " Li Chengrecalls, just began to hand into the group into the bay propaganda, beating drums, go to the village, the lively energy of a pass.

After more than 20 days in the village, Li began to have trouble sleeping. The night in the country comes earlier and quieter than in the city. He goes to bed at 9:30 every night, and often wakes up in the middle of the night in a daze, not knowing where he is. The longer the outbreak lasts, the greater the anxiety. Many of my colleagues in the village suffered from the same symptoms -- insomnia.

Li Cheng described it like this: There is an invisible enemy, like nothing, you can feel, but not touch, can only wait hopeless. He felt like he was reaching his limit in every way. Road Closure, publicity, quarantine, disinfection and sterilization, household investigation, buying drugs and gas, procurement of materials... These things vividly, but not clear yesterday and today.

Rework, Spring Ploughing countdown, waiting for a complete release

How long the grass-roots epidemic prevention will last, Li Cheng still do not know.

He ate two meals a day (breakfast and lunch together) because of the trouble of cooking and the lack of food. "At the beginning, because I had to go to the village for a long time, if I didn't eat in the morning, I was very hungry one day, so now I have to cheer up every morning and make a good meal. " When he set out on February 2, he took 8 Jin of rice and 3 Jin of noodles with him until the 20th day, and ate half of it.

Although he had made up his mind not to go home during his stay in the village, he went back the day after the Lantern Festival. Five hours, two hours on the road, half an hour to go home, eat a meal, take some preserved meat, preserved fish, and immediately return to the village.

Stay in the village for a long time, the attitude of the villagers to Li Cheng also quietly changed. A family of children's birthday, also sent him a few steamed stuffed Bun. Li Cheng took a picture and sent out a friend circle saying: It's been a long time since I ate steamed stuffed Bun. This plot, but also let him remember the first to the villagers home temperature measurement, those who speak of indifference and alienation. And once to collect Mahjong, the villagers also threatened to Upload Video, to the court.

Under the threat of the epidemic, villagers have to accept the status quo whether they like it or not. Recently, Li Chenga friend in the village, an old Chinese medicine coronary heart disease suddenly, unfortunately died. The doctor was of high moral standing, and he was seen by all the people in the village. "In normal times, when such an old man goes up the mountain, the whole village would cry and send him on his way. But under the haze of the epidemic, everything was simplified and the old man's funeral was dealt with that day. "

However, in this season, the villagers there is a major event is not to delay, that is the upcoming spring plowing. Some people are bound to do farm work and buy seeds and fertilizer. Lee admitted that Guan, after all, is not shut down.

The rework has begun. Sun Yi revealed that it is necessary for the enterprise or unit where the Party is located to issue a certificate agreeing to rework. After the party applies, the village will then, according to the health condition of this period of time, send the documents for going through the formalities for resuming work to the town government, the town government unified report to the county epidemic prevention headquarters, after being approved, Sun Yi here again. Sun Yi in the village of the total 212 home, has been released 24 people, most of them to Guangzhou.

Another problem is that many expectant mothers have difficulty in getting around. The township health centers are not insured, and it is not easy to go to the city. When they go to a place, they have to be quarantined. Li Cheng once advised a pregnant woman, try not to go to the prenatal examination, but that is also a kind of helpless compromise.

As of 2400 hours on February 24, there had been no new confirmed cases in the prefecture for four consecutive days. Everyone's waiting to see when we can finally unseal it.
